Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/src/libjasper/heic/heic_dec.c\n+++ b/src/libjasper/heic/heic_dec.c\n@@ -195,6 +195,11 @@\n     /* Get a handle to the primary image. */\n     heif_context_get_primary_image_handle(ctx, &handle);\n+    if (!handle) {\n+        jas_logerrorf("heif_context_get_primary_image_handle failed: handle is NULL\\n");\n+        goto error;\n+    }\n+\n     int width = heif_image_handle_get_width(handle);\n     int height = heif_image_handle_get_height(handle);\n     JAS_LOGDEBUGF(1, "width %d; height %d\\n", width, height);\n'}`
responded: The root cause of the null dereference is that `handle` may be NULL after the call to `heif_context_get_primary_image_handle(ctx, &handle);`, but the code does not check for this before dereferencing `handle` in calls like `heif_image_handle_get_width(handle)` and, crucially, in `heif_decode_image(handle, ...)`. If `handle` is NULL, this will cause a segmentation fault.

**Correct Fix:**
- Check if `handle` is NULL after `heif_context_get_primary_image_handle`.
- If it is NULL, log an error and goto the error handling section before any dereference.

Here is the patch:

```diff
--- a/src/libjasper/heic/heic_dec.c
+++ b/src/libjasper/heic/heic_dec.c
@@ -195,6 +195,11 @@
     /* Get a handle to the primary image. */
     heif_context_get_primary_image_handle(ctx, &handle);
+    if (!handle) {
+        jas_logerrorf("heif_context_get_primary_image_handle failed: handle is NULL\n");
+        goto error;
+    }
+
     int width = heif_image_handle_get_width(handle);
     int height = heif_image_handle_get_height(handle);
     JAS_LOGDEBUGF(1, "width %d; height %d\n", width, height);
```

This patch ensures that the program will not dereference a NULL pointer, thus fixing the vulnerability. I will now validate this patch.

